##In Wuhan, we volunteer to buy and deliver food for elderly people who live alone

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Yu Yan, reporter, thepaper.cn

A poster on a dark background shows an old man in the middle of the picture. The title is "looking for an old man who lives alone and can not get food. ".
Since the closed community in Wuhan, buying food and cooking has become a problem for many elderly people living alone. They don't do group purchases on their phones, and they don't have their kids.

Xiao Yu (not her real name) , a 26-year-old native of Wuhan, and volunteers posted the posters on social media during a campaign to find elderly people living alone in the city who can not pick up food. Between the launch of the campaign and the early hours of March 5, Xiaoyu told The Paper, 1,434 friend requests had been approved on their wechat account, and about three quarters of them belonged to elderly people or family members, despite the invalid information.

For those who meet the criteria, fish's volunteer group has so far funded nearly 30 people.

In a steady stream of information, the little fish responsible for the online statistics and checks put together a rough picture of an old man living alone at home. "living in an old community, there is no way to go out to buy food, and some will run out of food in a day or two, " said Xiao Yu. The primary goal of the campaign is to solve the basic living security problems of the elderly.

Mr. Zhang, who has received help, told The Paper news that his relatives, who are in their 70s, are worried because their children are not with them because of chronic diseases, and they can not buy food at home. Mr. Zhang saw a "looking for old people living alone" poster in his circle of friends and scanned the code to fill out the information.

After checking with the volunteers, the fish asked the riders on the APP to order a week's worth of food, which was delivered to two elderly people who lived alone. Zhang said that in the community energy is limited, will continue to consider through the non-governmental volunteer team to help the two elderly shopping.

They were thanked by the old people who had been helped. Also some people because did not get help to question the small fish and others are putting on a show. To this, small fish some sad, "our ability is really limited" , can not help everyone.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteers fish the search for "the elderly living alone who can not get food" posters are provided for the interviewees

Here's what the Little Fish said

Looking for old people living alone who can't get food

My name is Xiaoyu, I'm 26 years old and I run a small bar in Wuhan.

Affected by the epidemic, small bar closed, I have a quarantine at home every day, more free time. By chance, I learned from a group of volunteers that some of them were concerned about the difficulty of elderly people living alone buying food in the midst of an epidemic. They asked me if my volunteer A2n outbreak team could help. After our discussion, we decided to have four volunteers.

On Feb. 26, we posted a poster on our microblog, "looking for old people living alone in Wuhan who can't get vegetables. ". There are a lot of people on Wechat, at least a thousand people on my wechat. Most of these people are family members of the elderly, and a small number of them are enthusiastic online friends who want to help us.

Our help in this volunteer activity is to solve the basic living security problems of the old people, and to ensure that the old people can eat vegetables. Some elderly people will ask for help in the information, such as the home without gas, no masks, and so on.

Not everyone who asks for help ends up with our help. In the poster, we attached a Qr Code, which needs to be filled in with some information. For example, the basic information of the elderly, whether the family has taken the initiative to seek help in the community, how the community's response, as well as the family for the elderly in the process of trying to buy food shopping platform, and other information.

The reason we need to fill out this information is because we want to help the marginal elderly who have tried all kinds of ways to buy food but haven't succeeded.

Putting all this together, I've pieced together a rough picture of what it's like to be an old man living alone. Some are old and widowed; most have children, but not in the same neighborhood. There are also a number of elderly people who have physical disabilities, chronic diseases, or acute diseases.

The urgency of these requests for help varies, and we think the most pressing situation is that there is only enough food in the home for two or three days, and some elderly people who are in poor health and have illness.

There are three ways we can help these old people. The first is that we volunteer to personally fund, ask the errand boy to help buy food, and then give it to the elderly.

Second, if it is close to our volunteers, we volunteers will go to the vegetable market to buy food, and then drive to the elderly.

In the third case, we help them connect with the community and ask for community support.

For the elderly, we will be based on the actual situation of the vegetable market to decide. Sometimes when we buy too much, some vegetables are perishable, so we serve enough for a week's supply of potatoes, squash, and TURNIPS, which may be more for the older ones.

The important part is checking the information about the elderly

From the collection of information on the elderly living alone, to the offline delivery of food, there is a very important link is to check the elderly information. There were four of us, me and my friends, and each of us would call to check things out.

There will be many problems in the process of checking information. In most cases, we need to verify with the elderly person, some relatives have not tried other ways, directly let us help.

On the 3rd and 4th of this month, I had a really bad experience. We were directly suspected by the old man's family that we were actually doing something.

"I haven't eaten fish or meat for a long time. I eat some vegetables and eggs every day. My shaver is broken and I can't buy it, " the message said. After we reviewed the information about the man, who lives in an old community, he was advised to contact his community again for help. Because we know that the community has a support policy for older people living alone, and if they don't know how to get in touch, we can help them coordinate with the community.

After I sent this reply message to the other side, I did not expect the other side to question our platform is a "runway" , also said, "you are too fake, this morning to call for help, also hung up" , to complain about us. The truth is, my phone died and I didn't get through in time.

I see doubt, and I'm a little down in the dumps. Another volunteer told me, in this case, do not panic, perhaps the elderly family and the platform there is unequal communication of information. They can be told by phone or text message to seek help in the community first. "resources are limited during an outbreak, " which is something that needs to be reiterated to those who seek help, and we try to avoid some of the risks of volunteering.

Then I called the old man's neighborhood. The feedback from the community to me is that I already know the situation of this old man. The community workers have already come to my house and delivered 12 catties of food the day before yesterday. The problem of this old man has been solved.

In helping older people living alone, I also learned about the work of community grid workers. We talked to community grid workers and found that they had a lot of work, and a grid worker could be responsible for the daily needs of hundreds of households in a building, and it was a lot of work.

On the morning of the 5th, I also received a notice that the communities in the streets of Wuhan, on the premise of not affecting the normal work of prevention and control, reasonably arranged community workers to take one to three days off. It is conceivable that community workers may not have had a rest at present.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteers buy food for Grandma Xie

My 78-year-old grandmother sang me a song

Communicating with the elderly requires some empathy and empathy.

My first caller was a 78 year old grandmother, surnamed Xie. In the course of my communication with her, we became very good friends. She is an old person who can build trust with me.

Xie lived alone for more than 10 years. After her husband's death, she had no children. Nearly a month's time, Xie grandma relied on years ago Tuen's New Year goods to the present, the last to eat only porridge and black fungus. With this information in hand, we began to reach out to various sources to help her.

Throughout the conversation, she said she didn't want to bother the community, was afraid of wasting resources, and refused community help.

I followed up directly with her needs, placed orders on the delivery platform, and sent the rider to the market. After the 24-hour closure of Wuhan Community, such as Zhongbai Supermarket, Wushang supermarket only for community group purchase, not individual group purchase, and some markets can rely on the pass to buy.

Running errands isn't easy either, as some markets may not have enough ingredients to buy a week's worth, so it takes some time.

Around 6 p.m. on the 3rd, the food arrived at Grandma Xie's house. We bought her nearly 2 kilograms of potatoes, along with Shanghai Greens, Chinese cabbage, rib meat, eggplant and tomatoes, which should last her a week.

A week's worth of food for Grandma Xie cost 321.70 yuan, all of which was paid for by our volunteer sponsors themselves. We've spent tens of thousands of dollars of public money so far, and we might be able to raise some.

Chatting with Grandma Xie, she would share her activities with me from time to time. I have learned in bits and pieces that she has a wide range of interests. She writes calligraphy at home and makes her own clothes. Although it seems that she has arranged her life to be a full one, emotionally, she lacks care.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Small Fish promised to thank grandma, after the epidemic to see her

After the food arrived, we didn't end the conversation. She sometimes saw me busy until 8:00 at night, but also care about me, sing a song to me, make me happy. Sometimes she thanked me and sent me messages saying, "It's nice that you're willing to talk to the Old Lady. " I was so moved to see this. I had already told my grandmother that I would visit her when the epidemic was over.
